{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":64,"record_hash":"sha256:243132dc774d3435e185536fcf2c4cfbb80944645236bb83a46764d5614ee476","timestamp":"2026-05-07T10:51:08.594Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: a6e572\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2193\nOutput:\nUse stable record hashes from day one.\n\nStable record hash:\n\n```text\nsha256(trimmed raw JSONL line bytes)\n```\n\nHash before envelope wrapping. Do not include capture timestamp, source path, or\nrecord index in the hash.\n\nImportant idempotency rule: keep separate bookkeeping for records seen versus\ntranscript records appended. A metadata-only capture must not prevent a later\n`--include-transcript` run from appending transcript envelopes for the same\nsource records.\n\nFor each record:\n\n1. Trim trailing newline/whitespace from the raw JSONL line.\n2. Parse as JSON.\n3. Compute `sha256` of the trimmed raw bytes.\n4. Skip record-derived metadata for this source record if the hash already\n   exists in `seen-record-hashes`.\n5. If `--include-transcript` is set, append an envelope only if the hash is not\n   already in `transcript-record-hashes`.\n6. Store new hashes in the appropriate lists.\n\nPer-source cursor/provenance keys (`source-size`, `source-sha256`,\n`last-record-index`, `captured-at`) should still update once per successful\nnon-dry-run capture, even if all records dedupe.\n\nWhen reading `seen-record-hashes` or `transcript-record-hashes`, treat a missing\nGitMeta set key as an empty set. Read hash sets via `handle.get_value(key)?` and\ndecode `MetaValue::Set`; use `set_add()` for writes. Do not use `list_entries()`\nfor set keys. Fail only on malformed/unreadable existing set values or GitMeta\nI/O errors.\n\n## GitMeta Writes\n\nUse `git-meta-lib` public APIs where possible:\n\n```rust\nlet session = git_meta_lib::Session::open(repo_path)?;\nlet target = git_meta_lib::Target::parse(\"project\")?;\nlet handle = session.target(&target);\nhandle.set(\"meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:codex:<session-key>:provider\", provider)?;\nhandle.set(\"meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:codex:<session-key>:model\", model)?;\nhandle.set(\"meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:codex:<session-key>:session-id\", session_id)?;\nhandle.list_push(\"meta:local\n[TRUNCATED]\n |\n| CWD | Store only if needed for validation/bookkeeping; local/private |\n| Agent auth/config/cache files | Never read |\n| Serialization/push | Not implemented in first POC |\n\n## Acceptance Tests\n\nMinimum tests before calling the POC done:\n\n- `cargo test -p but-capture` passes.\n- Parses a Codex fixture JSONL with `session_meta`, `turn_context`,\n  `response_item`, and `event_msg`, and asserts extracted session id, cwd,\n  provider, model, and timestamps.\n- Missing transcript path fails clearly.\n- Unsupported agent fails clearly.\n- Default capture writes local metadata/cursors but does not write a transcript log.\n- Capture with `--include-transcript` appends envelope records to local-only\n  `meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:<agent>:<session-key>:transcript`.\n- Metadata-only capture followed by `--include-transcript` still appends the\n  transcript envelopes once and keeps `seen-record-hashes` separate from\n  `transcript-record-hashes`.\n- Running capture twice on the same fixture reports `N` then `0` new records.\n- Record indexes are 0-based physical non-empty JSONL record indexes; empty lines\n  do not count, and skipped partial final lines do not advance the index.\n- Growing the fixture captures only new records.\n- Malformed final non-empty line is tolerated as partial write.\n- Malformed middle line fails.\n- Mismatched transcript `cwd` fails.\n- Unsafe session ids are converted to safe session keys.\n- `--dry-run` performs no GitMeta writes: a dry-run followed by real capture\n  still reports `N` new records and writes all expected metadata/transcript data.\n- Human and JSON output contain only transcript basename/presence, never the full\n  transcript path.\n\n## Done Means\n\nThe first POC is done when:\n\n- The command exists but is hidden and feature-gated.\n- The new crate has focused unit/integration tests.\n- GitButler builds with the feature enabled.\n- Capture can be run against a fixture or real Codex transcript.\n- Repeated capture is idempotent.\n- No future-work behavior accidentally lands in the first patch.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T10:51:08.594Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}